D

DirectedGraph - Class in com.regex.sre.graph
The DirectedGraph class is written to support the simple regular expression parsing done using non-deterministic finite automata approach.
DirectedGraph(int) - Constructor for class com.regex.sre.graph.DirectedGraph
A constructor which takes in the number of vertices in the graph as an input and initializes an empty DirectedGraph
DirectedGraphDFSUtils - Class in com.regex.sre.graph
The DirectedGraphDFSUtils class is written to traverse the DirectedGraph using DFS and mark the visited vertices true, which is in turn used in simple regular expression parsing done using non-deterministic finite automata approach.
DirectedGraphDFSUtils(DirectedGraph, int) - Constructor for class com.regex.sre.graph.DirectedGraphDFSUtils
Given a DirectedGraph and a source vertex, this method computes all the vertices that can be reached starting from source and marks them in the marked array
DirectedGraphDFSUtils(DirectedGraph, HashBag<Integer>) - Constructor for class com.regex.sre.graph.DirectedGraphDFSUtils
Given a DirectedGraph and a HashBag containing the adjacent vertices to a source vertex, this method marks all the vertices that can be reached from the vertices in the bag as true in the 'visited'
